      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Measures and weights are of the nature of case-relationship.<note place="foot">i.e. if <foreign xml:lang="ta">āyiram</foreign> is followed by words denoting measures <foreign xml:lang="ta">(aḻavu)</foreign> and weights <foreign xml:lang="ta">(niṟai),</foreign> the <foreign xml:lang="ta">sandhi</foreign> change is the same as in case-relationship, e.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">āyirakkalam'</foreign> 'one
          thousand <foreign xml:lang="ta">kalams</foreign> <corr>(</corr>lit. vessels', or <foreign xml:lang="ta">
          āyirakkaḻañcu</foreign> ' one thousand <foreign xml:lang="ta">kaḻañcus '.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
